This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel estimator to speed up the learning process of a well-known undirected topic model. It also mentions experiments on two benchmarks to evaluate the efficiency and accuracy of the proposed estimator, which is a common practice in the field of machine learning. 

Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as document retrieval and classification, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). 

Furthermore, the paper deals with the extraction of semantic representations of documents, which is related to information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.IR and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. 

Finally, the paper mentions experiments on benchmarks that involve image classification, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision).
